gomodel:SYNGO_4712  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immunogold labelling identified Calmodulin in both the pre and postsynaptic compartment. In addition, a further quantitative analysis of immunogold identified a selective accumulation of Calmodulin immunoreactivity underneath the morphologically defined postsynaptic density. As the CALM 1-3 genes are expressed in the hippocampus, these pools of synaptic calmodulin could derive from any or all of the CALM genes.. Experimental description: M&M: \"Young Sprague-Dawley rats (postnatal day 5 or 6) were purchased from Charles River Laboratories\"\n\nantibody:\n\"CaM was labeled with an anti-CaM antibody (Epitomics, CA, USA) and an anti-rabbit antibody coupled to 10-nm gold particles (Electron Microscopy Sciences, PA, USA).\"\n\nImmunogen Synthetic peptide. This information is proprietary to Abcam and/or its suppliers. However the protein will recognize all calmodulin encoded by 3 non allelic genes that generate identical polypeptides." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-3185-5709" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4712" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

